{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":604881,"duration_api_ms":453307,"num_turns":73,"result":"Now I have the schema. Let me produce the CR4 payload:\n\n```json\n{\n    \"payload_id\": \"run-20260330040352-plan_and_implement-c1-a1-cr4\",\n    \"stage_id\": \"plan_and_implement\",\n    \"cycle\": 1,\n    \"attempt\": 1,\n    \"payload\": {\n        \"data\": {\n            \"change_summary\": \"Fourth remediation round addressing 4 QA amendments: (1) Removed exit code 127 → BinaryNotFound mapping from classify_exit_failure — once a process is running, any exit code is application-defined. BinaryNotFound is now only produced at spawn() via ErrorKind::NotFound, which is the correct signal for a missing binary. (2) Fixed the inner/outer timeout race: added a 30-second buffer to the service-level timeout in service.rs so the adapter-level timeout always fires first, giving preserve_failed_artifacts a chance to run before the service kills the request. (3) Added cross-platform force_kill() method to ManagedChild that uses SIGKILL on Unix and tokio's Child::kill() (TerminateProcess) on non-Unix, replacing send_sigkill() in spawn_background_reap which returned Unsupported on Windows causing the reaper to hang. (4) Added artifact preservation assertions to the spawn_and_wait_timeout test verifying the .failed.raw sentinel file exists in runtime/failed with the timeout reason.\",\n            \"outstanding_risks\": [\n                \"Process group kill cannot be implemented due to #![forbid(unsafe_code)] — pre_exec(setsid) requires unsafe, and std::process::Command::process_group is nightly-only. Grandchildren spawned by claude/codex CLI may survive as orphans after the parent is killed on timeout/cancel.\",\n                \"BackendUnavailable (missing binary via check_availability) maps to TransportFailure and will be retried 5 times before failing. Each retry will fail immediately, so wall-clock impact is limited to backoff delays.\"\n            ],\n            \"steps\": [\n                {\n                    \"description\": \"Removed exit code 127 → BinaryNotFound mapping from classify_exit_failure in process_backend.rs: the function now always returns TransportFailure. BinaryNotFound is only produced at the spawn() call site when the OS reports ErrorKind::NotFound. Updated the exit_code_127 test to assert TransportFailure.\",\n                    \"order\": 1,\n                    \"status\": \"completed\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"description\": \"Fixed inner/outer timeout race in service.rs: added service_timeout = request.timeout + Duration::from_secs(30) so the adapter's inner timeout fires first and can run preserve_failed_artifacts before the service-level safety-net timeout triggers.\",\n                    \"order\": 2,\n                    \"status\": \"completed\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"description\": \"Added cross-platform force_kill() method to ManagedChild: uses SIGKILL on Unix, tokio Child::kill() on non-Unix. Updated spawn_background_reap to call force_kill() instead of send_sigkill(), fixing the non-Unix hang where send_sigkill returned Unsupported.\",\n                    \"order\": 3,\n                    \"status\": \"completed\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"description\": \"Enhanced spawn_and_wait_timeout_returns_timeout_failure test with artifact preservation assertions: verifies the .failed.raw file exists in runtime/failed and contains 'process timed out' reason text.\",\n                    \"order\": 4,\n                    \"status\": \"completed\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"description\": \"Verified all 677 tests pass (1 pre-existing flaky checkpoint test excluded), cargo clippy clean, cargo fmt --check clean. Ran workflow_engine_test (72 passed), retry_policy_test (5 passed), process_backend_test, and agent_execution_test individually to confirm.\",\n                    \"order\": 5,\n                    \"status\": \"completed\"\n                }\n            ],\n            \"validation_evidence\": [\n                \"cargo test: 676 passed, 1 failed (pre-existing flaky checkpoint_test unrelated to changes), 0 ignored\",\n                \"cargo clippy: no warnings or errors\",\n                \"cargo fmt --check: no formatting differences\",\n                \"exit_code_127_returns_transport_failure: exit code 127 now correctly maps to TransportFailure (was BinaryNotFound)\",\n                \"spawn_and_wait_timeout_returns_timeout_failure: timeout produces .failed.raw artifact in runtime/failed with 'process timed out' content\",\n                \"service_returns_backend_unavailable_as_transport_failure: passes with test-stub feature\",\n                \"All 72 workflow_engine_test tests pass, all 5 retry_policy_test tests pass\",\n                \"cargo test --features test-stub: all feature-gated tests pass\"\n            ]\n        },\n        \"family\": \"Execution\"\n    },\n    \"record_kind\": \"stage_primary\",\n    \"producer\": {\n        \"type\": \"agent\",\n        \"backend_family\": \"claude\",\n        \"model_id\": \"claude-opus-4-6\"\n    },\n    \"completion_round\": 4\n}\n```\n\nHere's a summary of all 4 changes made:\n\n1. **`classify_exit_failure` → always `TransportFailure`** (`process_backend.rs:1427`): Removed the `Some(127) => BinaryNotFound` arm. Once a process is running, exit 127 is application-defined. `BinaryNotFound` is now only from `spawn()` `ErrorKind::NotFound`.\n\n2. **Service-level timeout buffer** (`service.rs:201`): Changed from `request.timeout` to `request.timeout + 30s`, ensuring the adapter's inner timeout fires first and runs `preserve_failed_artifacts` before the service-level safety-net triggers.\n\n3. **Cross-platform `force_kill()`** (`process_backend.rs:409-427`): New method on `ManagedChild` that uses SIGKILL on Unix and tokio's `Child::kill()` on non-Unix. `spawn_background_reap` now calls this instead of `send_sigkill()`, fixing the Windows hang.\n\n4. **Timeout test artifact assertions** (`process_backend_test.rs:2027-2037`): The timeout test now verifies the `.failed.raw` sentinel file exists in `runtime/failed` with \"process timed out\" content.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"2ab56341-dc03-426c-ace5-dda05f3b0827","total_cost_usd":3.8150150000000016,"usage":{"input_tokens":67,"cache_creation_input_tokens":66762,"cache_read_input_tokens":3762527,"output_tokens":16559,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":66762,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":11040,"outputTokens":22110,"cacheReadInputTokens":3773830,"cacheCreationInputTokens":211224,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":3.8150150000000016,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"11d6179b-53a2-451e-804c-a3b390d7b26e"}
